🚀 ORM kya hota hai?
👉 ORM = Object Relational Mapping

🧠 Simple samajh
👉 Database me data hota hai → tables me
👉 Java me data hota hai → objects me

👉 ORM = in dono ko connect karna

🔥 Example

Database table:
id | name | email

Java class:
class User {
    int id;
    String name;
    String email;
}

👉 ORM bolta hai:

“Main table ko object me convert kar dunga”

⚙️ Without ORM (JDBC)
ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery("SELECT * FROM student");

while(rs.next()) {
    String name = rs.getString("name");
}

👉 Tu manually:
- data read kar raha
- mapping kar raha

✅ With ORM
List<User> users = userRepository.findAll();

👉 Bas ek line
👉 ORM sab handle karega


🚀 Hibernate kya hai?
👉 Hibernate = Java ka most popular ORM tool (Basically ek sexy ORM tool hai)

🧠 Matlab
👉 ORM = concept
👉 Hibernate = us concept ka implementation

🔥 Example
Tu likhega:
userRepository.save(user);

👉 Hibernate internally karega:

INSERT INTO user ...

⚙️ Hibernate kya karta hai
- SQL generate karta hai
- DB se baat karta hai
- Data ko object me convert karta hai
- Relationships handle karta hai

SIMPLE FLOW:
Java Object → Hibernate → SQL → Database
Database → Hibernate → Java Object

| JDBC       | Hibernate  |
| ---------- | ---------- |
| Manual SQL | Automatic  |
| Complex    | Easy       |
| Low level  | High level |

🧠 Real Samajh (Important)
👉 Tu abhi JDBC kar raha hai
👉 Hibernate bolta hai: “Tu logic likh, DB main sambhal lunga”


*****************************************************************************************************

🚀 ORM (Hibernate) vs Without ORM (JDBC)

| Feature              | Without ORM (JDBC)          | With ORM (Hibernate)         |
| -------------------- | --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Level                | Low-level                   | High-level                   |
| SQL Writing          | Manual                      | Automatic (generated)        |
| Code Length          | More (boilerplate)          | Less (clean)                 |
| Data Mapping         | Manual (ResultSet → Object) | Automatic (Table ↔ Object)   |
| Maintenance          | Hard                        | Easy                         |
| Learning Curve       | Easy start, hard scale      | Slight start, easy scale     |
| Performance Control  | Full control                | Less control (but optimized) |
| Security             | Risky (SQL Injection)       | Safer                        |
| Development Speed    | Slow                        | Fast                         |
| Relationships (Join) | Manual SQL                  | Easy with annotations        |
| Example              | `SELECT * FROM user`        | `userRepository.findAll()`   |
| Focus                | DB-centric                  | Object-centric               |


***************************************************************************************************

🚀 Hibernate Architecture (Main Components)
Java App → Session → Hibernate → JDBC → Database

| Component      | Role                                   |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Configuration  | Hibernate setup (DB config, mappings)  |
| SessionFactory | Heavy object, creates Sessions         |
| Session        | Main object → DB se interact karta hai |
| Transaction    | DB operations ko control karta hai     |
| Query          | HQL/SQL run karne ke liye              |
| Entity         | Java class mapped to table             |
| Cache          | Performance improve karta hai          |

🔍 Ek-ek samajh le
⚙️ 1. Configuration
👉 Setup karta hai:
- DB connection
- Hibernate settings
Configuration cfg = new Configuration().configure();


🏭 2. SessionFactory
👉 Heavy object
👉 Ek hi baar banta hai
SessionFactory factory = cfg.buildSessionFactory();

👉 Kaam:
Sessions banana


🔄 3. Session (MOST IMPORTANT 🔥)
👉 Ye hi real worker hai
Session session = factory.openSession();

👉 Kaam:
- save()
- get()
- update()
- delete()


💸 4. Transaction
👉 Safe execution ke liye

Transaction tx = session.beginTransaction();
tx.commit();

👉 Ensure:
sab ya kuch nahi (Atomicity)


🔍 5. Query
👉 Data fetch karne ke liye

Query q = session.createQuery("from User");


🧱 6. Entity
👉 Java class = DB table

@Entity
class User {}


⚡ 7. Cache
👉 Performance improve karta hai
👉 Repeated DB calls kam karta hai


🔥 Flow Samajh (Important)
1. Configuration load
2. SessionFactory create
3. Session open
4. Transaction start
5. Operation (save/get)
6. Commit
7. Session close

🎯 One-Line Summary
Hibernate uses Session to interact with DB, SessionFactory to create sessions, and Transaction to manage operations safely.